* y : [0 .. n - 1] -> Complex
	* the output vector, the data points in fourier space ["frequency domain"]
* (y 0) is the shift, the mean of x
* multi-dimensional vectors
	* the DFT is separable
		* this is easy to prove
* when the input is real
